RACE.FOOTNOTES: DOLCE SERA broke a half-step slow then was hustled, raced towards the back under urging, moved closer near the half-mile pole, went three wide early on the turn, shifted five wide in the vicinity of the five-sixteenths, rallied outside coming to the quarter-pole, closed fast to get the lead into upper stretch, responded well into the final furlong and edged clear under steady urging. MOONEY MOONEY bumped soundly with a rival at the start, tracked the pace down the backstretch, chased in the four path around the turn, made a bid into upper stretch, chased the winner into the final furlong was outfinished while able to get the place. GRACEFUL lunged at the start then bumped soundly with a foe and was taken up, spotted the front several lengths, settled near the back under some urging, went four wide early on the turn, shifted six wide near the five-sixteenths, turned into upper stretch under a drive and finished willingly for the show. NOBLEANDGREENOUGH followed the leader while off the rail down the backstretch, chased in the three path under a bit of extra left-rein guidance around the turn, pursued the leader under a drive into upper stretch and weakened. BALENTINA was hustled to the front, showed the way with some company, vied inside while asked for more on the turn, lost the advantage to the winner into upper stretch and tired. HERECOMES SCARLETT lacked early speed and dropped back on the outside, raced under urging on the outside, angled in late on the backstretch, saved ground around the turn and failed to threaten. GERMANY JAYVO was hustled from the gate, pressed the pace on the outside, dropped back near the nine-sixteenths, went five wide early on the turn then was carried seven wide later on that bend and capitulated.

OUTER TURF FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD FOALED IN NEW YORK STATE AND APPROVED BY THE NEW YORK STATE-BRED REGISTRY WHICH HAVE NEVER WON $18,000 TWICE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING OR STARTER OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES OR OPTIONA L CLAIMING PRICE OF $45,000. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of Two Races Other Than Claiming Or Starter Since October 1 Allowed 2 lbs. Such A Race Since Then Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $45,000 (Allowance Horses Preferred)(1.5% A ftercare Assessment Due At Time Of Claim Otherwise Claim Will Be Void)(If No Three Year Olds Are Entered, Starting Weight Shall Be 122 lbs). (Rail at 24 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DERRYNANE broke out at the start bumping the shying out MOONAGE DAYDREAM into SHINFULL against pressure outside from PATRIA and ROAD TO REMEMBER, chased three then two wide before tipping back three wide nearing the quarter pole, swung four wide into upper stretch, offered up a good kick to rally and take command a sixteenth from home, dug in and prevailed on the wire. PATRIA crossed directly to the inside forcing ROAD TO REMEMBER to alter inwards at the start and crash into STARSHIP LAOBAN against pressure inside from DERRYNANE, forcing the two middle members of that quintet to get squeezed out, continued crossing until able to show the way in hand along the inside, came under coaxing at the five-sixteenths, spun just off the inside into upper stretch, dug in under a drive under threat to the outside and was collared a sixteenth from home, ran on willingly to secure the place honors. STARSHIP LAOBAN got squeezed out between foes at the start and was briefly taken in hand conceding four lengths to the front before settling into stride, chased three then two wide coming under coaxing at the five-sixteenths, went six wide into upper stretch, closed well outside to secure the show honors in the late stages. MOONAGE DAYDREAM shied out slightly at the start in reaction to the breaking out DERRYNANE and was bumped between foes conceding three lengths to the front, chased just off the inside under light coaxing to be forwardly placed, came under urging at the three-eighths, spun three wide for home, stayed on one paced tipping out near the sixteenth marker and was along for the last major share. SHINFULL got bumped between foes solidly and was squeezed out and steadied at the start getting away last and conceding four to five lengths to the front before being able to settle into stride, chased along the inside, came under coaxing nearing the quarter pole and spun just off the inside into upper stretch, tipped out to be three to four wide a furlong out closing in late, then had MOONAGE DAYDREAM tip out near the sixteenth marker to her inside and was taken back in hand and not persevered with late despite having a clear seam and finished under her own power. TEMPERMENTAL chased along the inside under coaxing from the five-sixteenths, angled four wide into upper stretch, dug in under a drive keeping on but was outkicked. ROAD TO REMEMBER broke in at the start as PATRIA tucked in from the outside and bumped STARSHIP LAOBAN into SHINFULL against pressure inside coming from DERRYNANE, chased four then three wide coming under coaxing at the five-sixteenths, swung five wide into upper stretch and weakened. There was a Stewards' Inquiry into the start as well as a claim of foul by the rider of STARSHIP LAOBAN alleging interference by PATRIA at the start. After review, the claim of foul was dismissed and the result was allowed to stand prior to the race being declared official.

ANILEATE got bumped between foes and pinched back at the start getting away last and conceding four to five lengths to the front before settling along the inside at the tail of the field, tipped two then briefly three wide through the first turn before settling three to four paths off the rail down the backstretch taking up the rear, began to steadily advance in the clear from the half mile pole into and through the far turn moving into prominence nearing the quarter pole now under coaxing, swung six wide into upper stretch and was floated out and bumped seven wide by SNOW LOVES A FIGHT straightened away before displacing that rival from the narrow and brief command she held nearing the eighth pole, dug in under a drive under threat to the inside, got guided in to get a look at her main danger and was overtaken a sixteenth out, ran on with good courage to be along clear of the rest and second best. HEARTBURN established the front and showed the way in hand along the inside patiently handled until set down spinning just off the inside into upper stretch, dug in and was collared straightened away into upper stretch, weakened in the late stages while prevailing in the battle for the show honors. SNOW LOVES A FIGHT just off the inside tracking the leader in closest aim, came under coaxing at the five-sixteenths, angled five wide into upper stretch and floated six wide bumping ANILEATE straightened away, seized brief and narrow command before being overtaken by ANILEATE near the eighth pole, dug in weakening in the late going. SMOKIN' HOT KITTY broke out at the start bumping ANILEATE and pinching that rival back in concert with pressure outside from ROSEMARY POTATOES, chased just off the inside until tucked inside through the far turn, came under coaxing at the five-sixteenths, swung four wide into upper stretch and offered no response. ROSEMARY POTATOES broke in at the start bumping ALWAYS LAUGHING into ANILEATE and causing half the pressure that pinched that foe back, chased just off the inside under coaxing from the five-sixteenths, angled six to seven wide into upper stretch and weakened. CROSS ISLAND two to three wide in pursuit, came under coaxing three furlongs from home, went six to seven wide into upper stretch and came up empty. RICELLE tracked the pace along the inside, got set down angled three wide into upper stretch, had the rider look back over their right shoulder and tipped out one additional path straightened away, then weakened to the finish. CRYSTAL ORB three wide through the first turn, chased three then two wide under coaxing from the three-eighths, tipped four wide into upper stretch, tired.
